# cppcheck suppressions for the pio-simulator static-analysis gate.
#
# Genuine false positives are suppressed inline, in the source next to the code
# (grep for "cppcheck-suppress"), so the justification lives with what it excuses.
# This file only silences cppcheck's own environmental / informational output —
# not findings about our code.

# We deliberately don't feed cppcheck the system include path (it analyses our
# sources, not libc), so it can't open <stdint.h> etc. Expected, not a finding.
missingIncludeSystem

# Informational epilogue, not a defect: the "active checkers" summary line.
checkersReport

# Informational: cppcheck caps branch analysis unless --check-level=exhaustive.
# We run the normal level on purpose; this note isn't a finding.
normalCheckLevelMaxBranches
